{"abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a time zone, at no particular point in time."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZoneProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"text":" struct is refcounted and immutable.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Each time zone has an identifier (for example, ‘Europe\/London’) which is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"platform dependent. See [ctor","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.TimeZone.new"},{"type":"text","text":"] for information on the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identifier formats. The identifier of a time zone can be retrieved using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.TimeZone.get_identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A time zone contains a number of intervals. Each interval has an abbreviation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to describe it (for example, ‘PDT’), an offset to UTC and a flag indicating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if the daylight savings time is in effect during that interval. A time zone","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always has at least one interval — interval 0. Note that interval abbreviations"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are not the same as time zone identifiers (apart from ‘UTC’), and cannot be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed to [ctor"},{"code":"GLib.TimeZone.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every UTC time is contained within exactly one interval, but a given"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"local time may be contained within zero, one or two intervals (due to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"incontinuities associated with daylight savings time).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An interval may refer to a specific period of time (eg: the duration"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of daylight savings time during 2010) or it may refer to many periods"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of time that share the same properties (eg: all periods of daylight"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"savings time).  It is also possible (usually for political reasons)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that some properties (like the abbreviation) change between intervals"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without other properties changing."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTimeZone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timezoneprotocol"]}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/identifier","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/time_zone_ptr-osvz"],"generated":true},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/adjustTime(type:time:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/findInterval(type:time:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/getAbbreviation(interval:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/getIDentifier()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/getOffset(interval:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/isDst(interval:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/ref()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/unref()"]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:4GLib16TimeZoneProtocolP","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"protocol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","title":"TimeZoneProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TimeZoneProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZonePro